<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-GRAMMYS-QUOTES-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
QUOTES FROM THE GRAMMYS
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
 
By DAILY NEWS STAFF 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   ``It's been 23 years (since I last hosted the Grammys). In fact,
back then, Madonna really was a virgin.'' _ Andy Williams.
</P>
<P>
   ``I doubt that.'' _ Phil Collins.
</P>
<P>
   ``We don't write these skits.'' _ Macy Gray.
</P>
<P>
   ``Hey! Peace and love! Yeah!'' _ Erykah Badu, accepting the Best
Rap Duo or Group Grammy with the Roots.
</P>
<P>
   ``What the hell was that, and why did it scare me to death?'' _
Rosie O'Donnell, on Kid Rock's performance.
</P>
<P>
   ``Oh, my God, you guys _ I seriously do not have a speech
prepared.'' _ Christina Aguilera, before rattling off what was
possibly the longest laundry list of thank-you's of the evening.
</P>
<P>
   ``This is the first time in the last five or six years where I'm
sure no one is looking at me.'' _ David Duchovny to Jennifer Lopez,
who was clad in only the loosest definition of the word.
</P>
<P>
   ``We want to thank Dennis Franz for playing (in their music
video) a guy who gets killed with black-eyed peas _ that takes a
real man.'' _ Natalie Maines of the Dixie Chicks, accepting the
Grammy for Best Country Performance.
</P>
<P>
   ``I just can't imagine that God's up there in heaven saying,
`Let's see now _ I've got to end world hunger, I've got to cure
AIDS, and I've got to make sure Whitney Houston wins that
Grammy!''' _ Rosie O'Donnell, on the priorities of the Person most
thanked during the ceremony (Clive Davis was a close second).
</P>
<P>
   ``Shania (Twain) couldn't be here tonight _ she's having her
belly waxed.'' _ Clint Black, after Twain won the Grammy for Best
Female Country Vocal Performance.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's important for future generations of artists and future
music fans to understand the importance (of classical music).'' _
Classical Producer of the Year Adam Abeshouse on the relative
obscurity of classical music in the Grammy process.
</P>
<P>
   ``We started out 28 years ago as a street band in Philadelphia,
so its pretty amazing that we can be here.'' _ Jay Crush, who won
for Best Classical Crossover Album.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's hard to describe any music with words. The thing we're
grateful about is it has finally given us a section in the record
store where we can find our music. I would call it Earth music
because we really aspire to celebrate the creatures and cultures of
the earth.'' _ Paul Winter, a winner for Best New Age Album. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   ``We called the album `Ancient Tones' because there was just a
lot of old sounds that are still around we loved. Those ancient
tones are still around today, you just have to hear them with your
heart and soul. It's Americas music. We want to make sure the next
generation gets a full dose of this music. _ Ricky Skaggs,
accepting the Grammy for Best Bluegrass Album _ ``Ricky Skaggs and
Kentucky Thunder: Ancient Tones.''
</P>
<P>
   ``It's great to see that Latin jazz music is growing all over
the world, and also, I think the commercial music you're more or
less speaking of is helping Latin music in general. The Latin
people have a lot to offer, a lot of flavor. _ Poncho Sanchez, who
won for Best Latin Jazz Performance for ``Latin Soul.''
</P>
<P>
   ``In 1955, Mehalia Jackson received the first Gospel Grammy and
in 1977, Shirley Caesar won the second. And in the year 2000, I am
still winning Grammys.'' _ Shirley Caesar, who won for Best
Traditional Soul Gospel Album for ``Christmas With Shirley
Caesar.''
</P>
<P>
   ``Well, I'm not Ricky Martin, I'm not Marc Anthony, and I'm sure
not Jennifer Lopez.'' _ Tito Puente, on the young generation of
Latin Pop Artists.
</P>
<P>
   ``She's one of my heroes, one of the greatest women I've ever
known.'' _ Emmylou Harris on collaborator Dolly Parton (the two won
Best Country Collaboration With Vocals along with Linda Ronstadt).
</P>
<P>
   ``The project chose me. When it was time to put the work on
tape, I got the call. We recorded some of Dr. King's speeches in my
voice, and some of his more famous, he did. For the actor in me, it
was a fairly daunting task. When you read some of Dr. King's
speeches in their entirety, I realized what a beautiful wordsmith
he was. It was important for me to really focus on the essence of
the content.'' _ Levar Burton, Best Spoken Word Album, ``The
Autobiography of Martin Luther King Jr.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I thought the talent I was up against was extraordinary. To be
nominated in any category is an achievement. I'm glad I wasn't in
any categories (Santana) was in.'' _ Sting, winner Best Male Pop
Vocal Performance for ``Brand New Day.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
