<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-24 01:43 </DATE_TIME>
<HEADER>
A6866 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN-(SLAN     02-24 0707
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKERS-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
LAKERS ARE 9-0 ON THIS WIN STREAK
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   CLEVELAND _ A bit of history was on the Los Angeles Lakers'
schedule Wednesday night. But for them to do what no past Lakers
team had ever done, they needed a low-scoring role player to reach
into his own past and retrieve an artifact from his early career.
</P>
<P>
   You remember Robert Horry's 3-point shot?
</P>
<P>
   Horry does and he relishes the rare opportunity to show he's
still got it. That chance came early Wednesday night and Horry
capitalized. He hit four 3-pointers in five tries and tallied a
season-high 20 points in the Lakers' 116-98 rout of the Cleveland
Cavaliers at Gund Arena.
</P>
<P>
   It was a performance reminiscent of Horry's earlier days with
the Houston Rockets. And it helped the Lakers achieve what no team
in franchise history had _ a perfect 6-0 road trip.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm proud of Rob. Rob stepped up tonight,'' said Shaquille
O'Neal, whose early foul trouble opened the door for Horry. ``We
have a lot of weapons on this team. On any given night, any one of
those players that comes off the bench can do that. If we had
somebody come off the bench and do that every night, we'd be a real
dangerous team.''
</P>
<P>
   As it stands, they're a 43-11 team, once again tied with the
Portland Trail Blazers for the league's best record, and have a
nine-game winning streak to go with earlier streaks of 16 and
seven.
</P>
<P>
   And then there's the fact they just swept a six-game trip
through the East, something even the Showtime Lakers never did. The
previous best for a six-game trip was a 5-1 mark by the 1967-68
team.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's one of those mileage points,'' coach Phil Jackson said,
``little checkpoints in a long season in which the team can look
back and be proud of and say we had to put it down, we had to be
real concentrated about our energy and about our direction. We had
to play with purpose and we did something that was very special.
And I think that's important for this team.''
</P>
<P>
   Kobe Bryant, who scored a team-high 21 points, said of the 6-0
mark: ``It meant a lot, considering all the great Laker teams that
have never done it. It's a good thing for us to build on.''
</P>
<P>
   It looked easier than it was and took some extraordinary efforts
from the supporting cast.
</P>
<P>
   Though Bryant also got seven rebounds and six assists, he looked
out of sorts on offense, hitting 9 of 22 shots. Glen Rice needed a
late charge in garbage time to get to 14 points (on 4-of-11
shooting). And O'Neal, who played just 10 minutes in a foul-marred
first half, finished with just 19 points.
</P>
<P>
   Picking up the slack were Horry (7 for 8 from the field), Ron
Harper (12 points) and A.C. Green (eight points). The bench
accounted for 42 points, 15 assists and 13 rebounds as the Lakers
shot 51.7 percent.
</P>
<P>
   ``What a game,'' Jackson said. ``It was just a very interesting
game tonight, the way it turned out.... Robert Horry came out on
fire stayed on fire for both halves, gave us the opportunity the
ballgame.''
</P>
<P>
   Horry, averaging 4.9 points, hadn't scored more than 12 in a
game this season. But he anchored the second unit early on and his
hot shooting led the Lakers to an 13-point lead in the second
quarter.
</P>
<P>
   ``Lately, even though I haven't been taking a lot of shots, my
shots are feeling pretty good,'' Horry said. ``Sometimes you just
have to take the shots when you have them. The offense is really a
good offense for me when you find an opportunity to shoot the
ball.... A lot of times we'll be hesitant to take the shots, so now
I'm just trying to be not as hesitant.''
</P>
<P>
   And the last time he scored 20? ``Shoot, it's been a long
time,'' he said with a laugh.
</P>
<P>
   Horry finished as strong as he started. He and O'Neal scored all
the points in a 10-2 run to start the fourth period and they
combined for 21 points in the final quarter.
</P>
<P>
   The Cavaliers responded by imploding, as leading scorer Shawn
Kemp (23 points) and Mark Bryant both earned ejections down the
stretch.
</P>
<P>
   The Lakers earned a trip home after 10 days on the road.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is a long trip,'' O'Neal said. ``I think I forgot where I
live at in L.A., we've been on the road so long.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
