may be a genuine voting bloc this year.
 &HT;    Gay rights may have been a throwaway debate line in South
Carolina. If it successfully mobilizes the nation's ``largest
voting bloc'' in upcoming primaries, it will become a centerpiece
issue by November.
 &HT;    No, the religious right is not finished. At least it is not
finished as a powerful political interest lobby. But _ if there was
ever any doubt _ it is finished as a ``religious'' entity. After
all, faithful Christians follow the Ten Commandments: ``You shall
not bear false witness against your neighbor.''
 &HT;    Yes, those are the same commandments the religious right is
lobbying for lawmakers to hang on schoolroom walls. Perhaps Reed
and Robertson should read them first.
 &HT;    
 &HT;    ----
