Milan. (Walton, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 20.
</P>
<P>
   NYFASHION-BACKSTAGE _ By the time I'd finished talking with the
backstage dressers at the recent New York runway shows, I was
thinking of signing up myself. It looked like fun. Hours before a
show begins, dressers are standing by racks of clothing, making
certain everything is in place. (Moss, Dayton Daily News). MOVED
EDs: Embargoed until Sunday, Feb. 27.
</P>
<P>
   NYFASHION-PRODUCER _ She shuffles the cards as proficiently as a
Las Vegas dealer and the stakes can be just as high. You won't see
spades or clubs on the stiff white cards Deborah Hughes holds as
she races up and down the aisles of a Bryant Park tent, stopping
only long enough to place or switch cards on chair seats as she
goes. The deck she holds is a ``who's who'' of the fashion world
and Hughes' expertise lies in knowing who should sit where: editors
from Vogue and Harper's Bazaar, writers from The New York Times and
The Washington Post, executives from Bergdorf-Goodman and Saks
Fifth Avenue, celebrities who come to support their favorite
designers. A faux pas can be disastrous. Hughes, 42, a former model
and public relations director for designer Carolina Herrera, is a
pro. (Moss, Dayton Daily News).50. MOVED
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed until Sunday, Feb. 27.
