<P>
   MOVIES-REINDEER _ Movie review: ``Reindeer Games'' with Ben
Affleck. (Murray, Atanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-BIGTEASE _ Movie review: ``The Big Tease,'' a lightweight
comedy about a hairdresser going to the olympics of hairstyling.
Grade: C. (Ringel, Atanta Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-WONDERBOYS _ Movie review: ``The Wonder Boys,'' from
director Curtis Hanson (``L.A. Confidential''). Grade: B.
(StMurray, Atanta Journal-Constitution). 21.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-DIGITAL _ PARK CITY, Utah _ On the surface, Chuck Collins
doesn't appear to be a movie industry mover and shaker. But
Collins, 44, is on a mission from Kennesaw to remake Hollywood.
It's one day before the start of the Sundance Film Festival, Robert
Redford's annual celebration of independent movies, which ended
Jan. 30, and Collins has traveled the nearly 2,000 miles here from
Atlanta to represent Cobb County's Digital Projection Inc. As DPI's
national market development manager, Collins is overseeing the
installation of roughly $1 million in cutting-edge projection
equipment that Sundance ultimately used to screen about 17 of its
112 films. The demonstration's ultimate impact portends to the
coming digital visual age in Hollywood. We report on Hollywood's
pending change to digital visuals, the controversy among filmmakers
and how the switch may alter what's shown at your local movieplex.
(BLongino, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 45. WITH PHOTO and
LAYOUTS.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed until Sunday, Feb. 27.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MINIREVIEWS _ Mini reviews of all currently playing
movies. (Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-WONDERBOYS _ Movie review of the ``Wonder Boys.'' The
Wonder Boys are actually Wunderkinds, which a German-English
dictionary translates as ``infant prodigies.'' Infant is perfect,
for, in different ways, these guys are a couple of pipsqueaks. They
can't even dispose of a dead dog. Three stars. (Schwan, Palm Beach
Post). 15.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-MRDEATH _ A review of ``Mr. Death.'' 3 stars. Eccentric
documentarian Errol Morris (``The Thin Blue Line'') studies one
Fred Leuchter, an execution-device designer who, not satisfied with
success in that cheerful field, took up a second career as a
Holocaust-denial ``expert.'' (Garcia, Austin American-Statesman).
18.
</P>
<P>
   REVIEW-REINDEER _ A review of ``Reindeer Games.'' 2 stars. A
former criminal wants to start a new life, but they just keep
pulling him back in. Ben Affleck, Gary Sinise and Charlize Theron
star. (Garcia, Austin American-Statesman).
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-SIMPATICO _ A review of ``Simpatico.'' 3 stars. Racetrack
scheme goes awry when romantic betrayal intrudes. Nick Nolte, Jeff
Bridges, Sharon Stone star in this adaptation of the Sam Shepard
play. (Macor, Austin American-Statesman). 13.
</P>
<P>
   MOVIES-REARWINDOW _ A look at the restored ``Rear Window,''
Hitchcock's supreme paean to the voyeuristic soul of the movie
experience. James Stewart and Grace Kelly were at their finest in
this masterful 1954 thriller. (Macor, Austin American-Statesman).
20. MOVED
</P>
