<P>
   BOOKS
</P>
<P>
   SKUBE-ON-BOOKS _ Michael Skube on E.L. Doctorow's new novel,
``City of God.'' (Skube, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   EDs: Embargoed until Sunday, Feb. 27.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-NOTES _ Until he was touched by an Oprah, North Carolina
native Robert Morgan was happy to sell 10,000 copies of his novels.
So far, ``Gap Creek'' has sold more than 600,000 since the author's
apperance on Winfrey's book club. Not bad for a high-school dropout
who grew up in a family who didn't own a car or a TV set and who
didn't see his first movie until he was 17. In other news,
Amazon.com has combined with PEN to launch another book award for
short-story writing with a $10,000 prize. (O'Briant, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 21.
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-KIDS _ Roundup of the latest children's books. (Bookman,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-LOVESUPREME _ Former Atlantans TaRessa and Calvin
Stovall's first book, ``A Love Supreme,'' is about a love barely
