r l BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX     02-24 0416
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
IT'S A WONDERFUL INFLATIONARY SPIRAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: In ``It's a Wonderful Life,'' Sam Wainwright cabled Bedford
Falls from London authorizing his local office to advance George
Bailey up to $25,000 to help him. How much would this money be
worth in today's dollars?
</P>
<P>
   _ R.B.M., Burleson, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: Assuming that the scene took place on Christmas Eve 1945,
Wainwright's offer was equivalent to $230,263 in current dollars,
according to an inflation calculator published by S. Morgan
Friedman.
</P>
<P>
   More inflation-adjusted figures from the 1946 film:
</P>
<P>
   The $8,000 Bailey Building and Loan deposit stolen by Henry
Potter is equal to $73,684 in current dollars.
</P>
<P>
   The $5,000 loan that William Bailey owed Potter in 1919 is like
$53,919 today.
</P>
<P>
   Also in 1919, George Bailey clicked a drugstore lighter and
wished for a million dollars. Children today must wish for
$9,210,532 to be equally enriched.
</P>
<P>
   Friedman's calculator uses Consumer Price Index statistics from
the Historical Statistics of the United States and the Statistical
Abstract of the United States. It's published on the Web at
www.westegg.com/inflation.
</P>
<P>
   Q: For many years, I had an American National Insurance policy.
Can you tell me if the company was purchased by someone else?
</P>
<P>
   _ L.W.S., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: American National Insurance continues to do business under
that name today and has 3.5 million policyholders. The company was
founded in 1905 and has its headquarters in Galveston.
</P>
<P>
   If your policy was life insurance, call American National at
(800) 899-6806 to inquire about it. Health insurance queries should
be directed to (800) 899-6503. You also can contact the company
through its Web site, www.anico.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Which Colorado town holds a Sweet Pea Festival every summer?
</P>
<P>
   _ J.M., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: A weeklong Sweet Pea Festival is held every August in
Bozeman, Mont., to celebrate the arts. The festival includes 5K and
10K runs, Shakespeare in the Park, bluegrass music and country
dancing, attracting crowds of up to 18,000.
</P>
<P>
   This year's event is scheduled for Aug. 4-6 in the city's
Lindley Park.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
