are. To attach the word ``women's'' to a cultural product is to
devalue it. In the view of the larger culture, ``women's'' is only
a step above ``young adult.''
 &HT;    Of course there are gender differences, although probably not as
many as there would be if this were a society in which men and
women could casually decide which gender wants to be president this
term, and which one wants to take care of the kids and
