consuming this substandard culture raises the heartbreaking
possibility that contemporary women's lives are so painful that
what they desire is a good cry and some brainless, narcotizing
amusement.
 &HT;    Hollywood appears to believe that women go to the movies to be
taken on a chain-yanking, tear-jerking, regressive journey down
