<P>
   DAY TRADING PROFITABLE _ FOR COMPANIES
</P>
<P>
   _ Most day traders do not make money, partly because their
trading costs are high. The average day-trading client makes 29
trades a day and pays $16 commission per trade. This means the
client must make profits of $464 a day _ or $111,360 a year if he
or she trades 20 days a month _ just to break even.
</P>
<P>
   _ The day trading industry saw its revenues climb 276 percent
between 1997 and 1999. The aggregate gross revenues of 15 top firms
in 1999 totaled more than $541 million, producing aggregate profits
of about $144 million.
</P>
<P>
   Source: Senate Permanent Investigations Subcommittee
</P>
<P>
   DAY TRADERS VS. OTHER STOCK OWNERS
</P>
<P>
   People owning stock........80 million
</P>
<P>
   Using online brokers.........5 million
</P>
<P>
   Day traders......................7,000
</P>
<P>
   Full-service brokerage customers ......... trade 6-12 times a
year
</P>
<P>
   Online investors ................................. trade 15-25
times a year
</P>
<P>
   Day traders ....................................... trade 29
times a day
</P>
<P>
   Sources: General Accounting Office, Senate Permanent
Investigations Subcommittee
</P>
<P>
   ENDIT
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
