   WASHINGTON
</P>
<P>
   SECRET-SERVICE _ WASHINGTON _ A group of black Secret Service
agents, including the agency's highest-ranking woman, said Thursday
the agency denied them promotions and key assignments because of
racial discrimination. The agents said at a news conference they
were seeking permission from the Equal Employment Opportunity
Commission to file a class-action lawsuit based on the allegations.
(Turay, Cox News Service). 20.
</P>
