U.S. Coast Guard, addresses a National Press Club luncheon on ``The
Future of the Coast Guard.'' (Livingston, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
<P>
   DAY-TRADING _ WASHINGTON _ Scott Webb moved to Atlanta thinking
``he was going to be rich and have a lavish lifestyle,'' his mother
told a Senate subcommittee Thursday. Instead, her 30-year-old son
plunged deeper into debt and depression before being shot to death
by a fellow day trader last July 29, said Alyce Wenzel. ``The loss
of my son continues to haunt me today,'' said Wenzel, testifying at
a hearing on the growing fast-paced stock market speculation.
(Dart, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 28. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
