<P>
   PRESTON-KING _ ALBANY, Ga. _ The funeral of Clennon W. King on
Thursday in Albany was more than a chance for Preston King to
reunite with relatives and friends, it became a touchstone for
black-white relations in the Southwest Georgia city. Everyone in
Albany says things have changed in the 39 years since Preston King
fled to avoid a prison sentence. Where they differ is on what his
action signified. (Campbell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25.
</P>
