<P>
   JCPENNY _ J.C. Penney's rush to acquire Eckerd and several other
drug store chains several years ago has come back to haunt it. The
department store chain now plans to close nearly 300 Eckerds and 45
of its department stores in the coming months in an effort to
bolster its bottom line. The developments came as J.C. Penney also
reported a larger-than-expected drop in fiscal fourth-quarter
profit and delayed for a second time the initial offering of a
stake in Eckerd. (DeGross, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   VENTURE-CAPITAL _ ATLANTA _ Advance on next week's high-powered
Red Herring venture capital conference. About 50 companies will
come to the Ritz next week to meet with hundreds of investors and
venture capitalists representing hundreds of millions _ if not
billions _ of dollars who are looking for promising start-ups.
(Kanell, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   DAY-TRADING _ WASHINGTON _ Scott Webb moved to Atlanta thinking
``he was going to be rich and have a lavish lifestyle,'' his mother
told a Senate subcommittee Thursday. Instead, her 30-year-old son
plunged deeper into debt and depression before being shot to death
by a fellow day trader last July 29, said Alyce Wenzel. ``The loss
of my son continues to haunt me today,'' said Wenzel, testifying at
a hearing on the growing fast-paced stock market speculation.
(Dart, Cox News Service). 28. WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
