</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Imagine a Long Island-set ``Magnolia'' directed by
early Jim Jarmusch with an assist from Edward Burns, and you have
some idea what to expect from ``Judy Berlin.'' Or maybe you don't;
if those names don't mean anything to you, it's a good indication
that you should pass on this ready-made cult movie. By ROBERT
PHILPOT. Story has moved in ``e'' entertaiment category. &QL; 
