<P>
   JOHNSON-COLUMN &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Watching a replay of Dennis Rodman tossing his jersey
to fans in Reunion Arena recently after being ejected from a game,
I thought of Jack Johnson, the first African-American heavyweight
boxing champion of the planet. Admittedly, it is a bit of reach to
connect the newest member of the Dallas Mavericks to someone like
Johnson. Despite being one tremendous athlete, Rodman will not rate
a footnote in the history of the progress of African-Americans
after he finishes strutting and fretting his bizarre hour on the
world stage. By CECIL JOHNSON. Story has moved in ``k'' commentary
category. &QL; 
